snippet.title: Abused Men
snippet.description:
New UK government campaign: https://petition.parliament.uk/petitions/585101
Please sign.
The latest version of  'Abuse - Monster in the House', is back on Amazon, including a chapter on Johnny Depp. The website, ad2045.com, is still being updated - apologies for the delays.

Gender wise, depending on which statistics/measurements you use, between 33 to over 50% of domestic abuse victims are reportedly male - yet, while technically criminal offences, very little seems to be done or even bothered about. 
Who hasn't seen a female shouting at a male or hitting him and simply found it amusing? For the victim it is anything but amusing. Males are generally stronger but in reality it is abused male vs abusive female plus the police, social services and the knowledge that if he dares ask them for help, even to save the kids, all she has to do is lie he is the abusiver and they can have him out the door, kids trapped with their abuser. This happens to many men. It almost happened to me.
